Commentary Text: Sam Curran to Warner, out Caught by Dhawan!! Dhawan pulls off a screamer! And out comes the thigh-slap! 109.6kph, slower delivery on a length, Warner looks to slap it downtown and ends up splicing it in the air. Dhawan runs across from cover and flies to his left to snaffle it out of thin air. The ball didn't pop out even when his arms hit the ground. Finally, PBKS have the breakthrough! Warner c Dhawan b Sam Curran 46(31) [4s-5 6s-2]
